<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="131" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1509,2076]" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">
Description: The subspecies differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[613,788,1509,1535]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Gymnomitriaceae" genus="Gymnomitrion" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="14" pageNumber="131" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="rubidum" subSpecies="rubidum">
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[693,788,1509,1535]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">rubidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in always narrowly revolute antical leaf margin and well differentiated ‘vitta’ in the leaf base (
<figureCitation box="[564,634,1545,1571]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="9.[136,229,1985,2007]" captionTargetBox="[183,1401,924,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-319@9.[177,1410,912,1964]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 4. Gymnomitrion rubidum subsp. subvittatum Vilnet, Bakalin &amp; D.G. Long: A—plant habit, fragment, lateral view; B—plant habit, fragment, ventral view; C, D—leaves; E—part of leaf base with ‘vitta’ cells. Scales: a—1 mm, for A, B; b—1 mm for C, D; c—100 µm for E. All from Long 34462 (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036345/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[649,665,1545,1572]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1499,1521]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1474]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[151,1436,190,1474]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Gymnomitrion rubidum subsp. subvittatum Vilnet, Bakalin &amp; D.G. Long: A—mat, dorsal view; B—part of leaf base with ‘vitta’ cells (reddish rusty colored group of cells); C, E—midleaf cells; D—leaf lobe cells. Scales: for A—5 mm; for B–E—50 µm. A, C, D from Long 20655 (E), B, E from Long 34462 (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036351" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036351/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[679,694,1545,1572]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[136,229,1188,1210]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,317,1164]" captionTargetId="figure-82@11.[151,1436,317,1164]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Gymnomitrion rubidum subsp. subvittatum Vilnet, Bakalin et D.G. Long: A—plant habit in dorsal and ventral views; B, C—lower part of leaf with ‘vitta’ cells. Scales: for A—1 mm; for B, C—300 µm. A from Long 20655 (E), B, C from Long 34462 (E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6036357" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6036357/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">6</figureCitation>
) as well as in several single base pair substitutions in ITS1-2 and 
<emphasis box="[136,169,1582,1607]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="131">trn</emphasis>
L-F.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
